# Project Rules: Next.js Full-Stack App

> Full-stack web application built with Next.js 14+ App Router, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.

## Project Identity

- **Type**: Full-Stack Web App
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Framework**: Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **ORM**: Prisma / Drizzle
- **Auth**: NextAuth.js v5
- **Testing**: Vitest + Playwright

---

## Coding Standards

### Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Pages | `page.tsx` (directory-based) | `app/dashboard/page.tsx` |
| Layouts | `layout.tsx` | `app/dashboard/layout.tsx` |
| Server Actions | camelCase with `Action` suffix | `createUserAction.ts` |
| Components | PascalCase | `UserCard.tsx` |
| API Routes | `route.ts` | `app/api/users/route.ts` |
| Utilities | camelCase | `formatDate.ts` |

### File Organization

```
app/
├── (auth)/            # Route group for auth pages
│   ├── login/page.tsx
│   └── register/page.tsx
├── dashboard/
│   ├── page.tsx       # Server Component (default)
│   ├── layout.tsx
│   └── loading.tsx
├── api/               # API Route Handlers
│   └── users/route.ts
├── components/        # Shared components
│   ├── ui/            # Base UI components
│   └── features/      # Feature-specific components
├── lib/               # Utilities, config, db client
├── actions/           # Server Actions
└── types/             # TypeScript types
```

---

## Critical Rules (🔴)

### Rule 1: ✅ Default to Server Components

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — unnecessary client component
'use client';
export default function UserList({ users }: Props) {
  return <ul>{users.map(u => <li key={u.id}>{u.name}</li>)}</ul>;
}

// ✅ GOOD — server component (no 'use client' needed)
export default async function UserList() {
  const users = await db.user.findMany();
  return <ul>{users.map(u => <li key={u.id}>{u.name}</li>)}</ul>;
}
```

### Rule 2: ❌ Never expose server secrets to client

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — leaks to client bundle
const apiKey = process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY;

// ✅ GOOD — server-only import
import 'server-only';
const apiKey = process.env.STRIPE_SECRET_KEY;
```

### Rule 3: ✅ Use Server Actions for mutations

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — API route for simple mutations
// app/api/users/route.ts + client fetch

// ✅ GOOD — Server Action
'use server';
export async function createUser(formData: FormData) {
  const name = formData.get('name') as string;
  await db.user.create({ data: { name } });
  revalidatePath('/users');
}
```

---

## Important Guidelines (🟠)

- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` for automatic loading/error states
- Prefer `<Image>` over `<img>` for automatic optimization
- Use `<Link>` for client-side navigation
- Implement proper metadata exports for SEO on every page

---

## Code Smells to Avoid

| ❌ Smell | ✅ Instead Do |
|----------|--------------|
| `'use client'` on every component | Default to Server Components |
| `useEffect` for data fetching | Fetch in Server Components |
| `getServerSideProps` | Use App Router `page.tsx` with async |
| Prop drilling across layouts | Use React Server Components + parallel routes |
| Manual `<head>` tags | Use `metadata` export or `generateMetadata()` |
